cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY 

This paper deals with optimization methods for machine learning, specifically for minimizing a strongly convex function represented as the sum of a large number of smooth convex functions. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the potential for parallelization, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on optimization methods could also fall under control and optimization (cs.SY).
